</para></solution>
</exercise>
</example>
<note id="fs-id1169596653516" class="try">
<exercise id="fs-id1169596653520">
<problem id="fs-id1169596653523">
<para id="fs-id1169596375236">Sam drives a delivery van. The equation <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>C</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>0.5</m:mn><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>60</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> models the relation between his weekly cost, <emphasis effect="italics">C</emphasis>, in dollars and the number of miles, <emphasis effect="italics">m</emphasis>, that he drives.</para>
<para id="fs-id1169751894665"><span class="token">ⓐ</span> Find Sam’s cost for a week when he drives 0 miles.<newline/>
<span class="token">ⓑ</span> Find the cost for a week when he drives 250 miles.<newline/>
<span class="token">ⓒ</span> Interpret the slope and <emphasis effect="italics">C</emphasis>-intercept of the equation.<newline/>
