<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1169594168892">
<term>parallel lines</term><meaning id="fs-id1169594168896">Lines in the same plane that do not intersect.</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1169594168900">
<term>perpendicular lines</term><meaning id="fs-id1169594168905">Lines in the same plane that form a right angle.</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1169594168910">
<term>slope-intercept form of an equation of a line</term><meaning id="fs-id1169594168914">The slope–intercept form of an equation of a line with slope <m:math><m:mi>m</m:mi></m:math> and <emphasis effect="italics">y</emphasis>-intercept, <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mi>b</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> is, <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mi>b</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>.</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
